Package: missingGroupr
Title: Count Missing Values by Group
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Sasha", family = "Sharma", email = "sasha.sharma@stat.ubc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a helper function that summarizes the number of
    missing values in all columns of a data frame when grouped by a
    specified column. This function wraps the dplyr verbs group_by(),
    summarize(), across(), and everything() to compute missing-value counts.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: dplyr
